[The results of the ongoing tests to confirm (or not) these recent
suspected YF cases are awaited with interest. - Mod.TY]

******
[2] Sao Paulo state
Date: Sun 5 Apr 2009
Source: O Globo [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://oglobo.globo.com:80/sp/mat/2009/04/05/mais-uma-pessoa-morre-com-suspeita-de-febre-amarela-em-piraju-no-interior-de-sp-755144250.asp>


One more person died Saturday [4 Apr 2009] with suspected yellow
fever [YF] in Piraju, 313 km [194 mi] from Sao Paulo [city]. The
victim, age 30 years, is the brother of another victim of YF who died
a week ago from the same disease. This is the 8th death in the city
of suspected yellow fever; 6 of these [cases] are confirmed, as well
as another 2 in central-west region of Sao Paulo [state] -- one in
Itatinga and one in Sarutaia.

According to the [Sao Paulo] state Secretariat of Health, 20 cities
in the region are in the [YF] risk area. In the municipality of
Itapetininga, the demand for vaccines increased and the supply is
gone. The Head of Surveillance Epidemiological said that he will
contact the government of the state to ask for more doses of vaccine.

--
